headline: 1 Consumer Stock to Target This Week and 2 to Turn Down
summary: Retailers are adapting their business models as technology changes how people shop. Still, demand can be volatile as the industry is exposed to the ups and downs of consumer spending. This has stirred some uncertainty lately as retail stocks have tumbled by 15.3% over the past six months. This performance was noticeably worse than the S&P 500’s 1.5% decline.
